7. oram Illyrici legis aequoris: leym-e, as a nautical term, means “to coast along.” Vergil imagines Pollio to be either coasting along Illyria or to have got as far as the Timavus as he was sailing round the Hadriatic homewards in 39 Ro. See Preface above.
